  <description><![CDATA[<p>Ski-in, ski-out access, rooftop spa facilities, and excellent cuisine make the adults-only Hotel Riml a ideal choice for guests looking for luxury in <a rel="noopener" data-udi="umb://document/5c5a68def0234451a0e7113b85bac993" href="/{localLink:umb://document/5c5a68def0234451a0e7113b85bac993}" target="_blank" title="Hochgurgl">Hochgurgl</a>. </p>
<h2>Ski-in, ski-out</h2>
<p>As well as ski-in, ski-out access, the Hotel Riml also has a hand in-house ski shop. At 7,218 feet on the Ötztal mountain, the hotel has a bird's-eye view over the valley. You can keep an eye on the piste from the hotel's sun terrace, a popular spot for skiers at lunch. </p>
<h2>Austrian welcome</h2>
<p>As you enter, the large lobby is decorated in pine and marble and has a cosy fire showcase. You are greeted in the lobby by the friendly local staff. Next door is the rustic dining room, bar, and suave a la carte restaurant.</p>
<p>Bedrooms are modern, comfortable and have pine décor. Some have balconies and we can’t get enough of the cinematic setting.</p>
<h2>Rooftop spa</h2>
<p>You can admire the snowy mountains from the adult-only rooftop spa with sauna, steam room and fitness room. The infinity pool on the mountainside is a must after a day on the slopes.</p>
<p>There is also an indoor golf putting course and golf simulator – to keep that swing in check.</p>
<p>The Hotel Riml is an adults-only hotel for ages 14+ years.</p>]]></description>
